Stanzione, Robert (Bob) J. - The Wall Street Transcript













































 





































Robert J. Stanzione
ROBERT J. (BOB) STANZIONE is Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of
ARRIS Group, Inc. Mr. Stanzione joined ANTEC in 1998 as President, Chief
Operating Officer and a Director and was appointed to the CEO role on
January 1, 2000. Prior to joining ANTEC he was the President and CEO of
ARRIS Interactive, a Nortel Networks/ANTEC joint venture. As ARRIS’
first President, Mr. Stanzione grew the venture from a startup company
to the world market leader in cable telephony products. From 1969 to
1995, he held a wide range of senior management positions with AT&T. He
holds a Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering from Clemson
University, a Master’s degree in Industrial Engineering from North
Carolina State University and has completed executive development
programs at the University of Richmond, Babson College and the
International Institute for Management Development in Switzerland. He
serves as a Director of CoaXmedia. He is a board member of the National
Cable & Telecommunications Association. He is a member of the Board of
Directors for the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation and also serves as Chairman
of the Georgia Cystic Fibrosis Major Gifts Campaign.
